X-ray diffraction (XRD) was used to analyze the crystal structure of pristine TiO2 and (Er3+/TiO2) NCs catalyst powders with different Er3+ ion concentrations, as shown in Fig. 4. The nanoparticles’ XRD configurations were found to be almost identical. As illustrated in Fig. 4, the intense peaks at 25°, 38°, 48°, 53°, 55°, and 62°, respectively, define TiO2 tetragonal anatase structure (Manoharan et al. 2014). As the Er3+ concentration increased, diffraction peak intensity reduced. The Scherrer formula was used to estimate the diameters of (Er3+/TiO2) NCs crystallites from XRD data:Fig. 4
